  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support Small Business to Fight Hunger in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The community of potters, formerly known as the &quot;Batwa&quot; pre-genocide, is a historically marginalized population that faces poverty and severe food shortages. To address the high prevalence of malnutrition in the community, HDI will help a community of 200 people to start a pig cooperative. The cooperative will give community members an income-generating activity to alleviate the effects of extreme poverty and provide the community with a rich protein source that will reduce malnutrition rates.</narrative>
  </description>
